lumn elementor-field-type-submit elementor-col-100 e-form__buttons\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<button class=\"elementor-button elementor-size-sm\" type=\"submit\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-content-wrapper\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<span class=\"elementor-button-text\">Send<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/span>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/button>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/form>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-5291f39 elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"5291f39\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-75fc867\" data-id=\"75fc867\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-568b6ee elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"568b6ee\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Where do furniture beetles live and what kind of furniture does their diet include?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-518a3ee elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"518a3ee\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Furniture beetles, also known as woodworms, are a type of beetle that primarily live and feed on wood. They can be found in various types of wood furniture, including chairs, tables, dressers, and cabinets. These insects prefer to live in environments with high humidity levels and warm temperatures. Therefore, they are commonly found in damp basements or attics where moisture is present.<\/p>\n<p>In addition to wooden furniture, furniture beetles also inhabit other structures made of wood, such as flooring and beams. Their diet includes hardwoods and softwoods like oak, ash, pine and spruce. Furniture beetles can cause significant damage to wooden structures by burrowing into the wood, creating tunnels that weaken the structure over time. This makes it important for homeowners to take preventative measures against infestations by ensuring proper ventilation in their homes and regularly inspecting any wooden structures for signs of infestation.<\/p>\n<p>The integrity of your furniture and home by tackling the menace of furniture beetles,&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/drugstore-beetles\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><u style=\"\"><b>drugstore beetles<\/b><\/u><\/a>,&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/grain-beetles\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><u><b>grain beetles<\/b><\/u><\/a>, and&nbsp;<a href=\"https:\/\/acmepestsolutions.com\/wood-cockroaches\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><u><b>wood cockroaches<\/b><\/u><\/a>&nbsp;with our effective pest control solutions.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-c1487f8 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"c1487f8\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Life Cycle: how do they reproduce?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-1735630 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"1735630\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Furniture beetles can reproduce through oviposition, which involves laying eggs in crevices or cracks in the wood. The larvae that hatch from these eggs damage wooden furniture and structures. These larvae feed on the cellulose in the wood and create tunnels as they grow.<\/p><p>Once fully developed, furniture beetle larvae transform into pupae and eventually emerge as adults. Adult furniture beetles mate and repeat the cycle by laying more eggs in suitable wooden environments. It is important to regularly inspect wooden structures for signs of infestation, such as small holes or sawdust-like debris, to prevent further damage from these pests. Treatment options include fumigation or replacing affected pieces of wood.<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-9654b5f elementor-section-full_width elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"9654b5f\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;,&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-0f3c876\" data-id=\"0f3c876\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-33 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-142af51\" data-id=\"142af51\" data-element_type=\"column\" data-settings=\"{&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;classic&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-elem