ementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"886306a\" data-element_type=\"section\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-container elementor-column-gap-default\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-column elementor-col-100 elementor-top-column elementor-element elementor-element-62596fe\" data-id=\"62596fe\" data-element_type=\"column\">\n\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-wrap elementor-element-populated\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-7a64132 elementor-widget elementor-widget-heading\" data-id=\"7a64132\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"heading.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t<h2 class=\"elementor-heading-title elementor-size-default\">Damage and Control: how can you get rid of furniture beetles?<\/h2>\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-482d10a elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"482d10a\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p>Furniture beetles are a common household pest that can wreak havoc on your furniture. These small insects lay their eggs in the cracks and crevices of wooden furniture, where the larvae hatch and begin to feed on the wood. Over time, this can lead to significant damage and deterioration of your furniture.<\/p><p>One of the most effective ways to eliminate furniture beetles is to freeze-infested items. This involves placing the affected piece of furniture in a freezer for several days, which will kill off any eggs or larvae present. Another option is using a chemical insecticide designed against wood-boring insects like furniture beetles.<\/p><p>Prevention is also key when it comes to controlling these pests. Regularly inspecting your wooden furniture for signs of damage, such as small holes or sawdust-like debris, can help you c